SourceTree crashed to desktop on startup.  On looking at the sourcetree.log file (attached), I noticed this line repeated many times...
{color:red}2015-08-29T11:13:23: Could not obtain git dir, D:\Projects\Tutorial is not a git repo.
{color}
I then created that folder and launched again without problem.  Apparently it's not handling deleted folders gracefully in the FileListViewManager...
{color:red}   at SourceTree.View.FileLists.FileListViewManager.DetermineIfStagingIsSupportedByDvcs(IFileListContainerViewModel parentFileListContainerViewModel) in C:\projects\bitbucket.org\atlassian\sourcetreewin-prod\SourceTree.Api.UI.Wpf\View\FileLists\FileListViewManager.cs:line 62
{color}
